---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Mermaid from '../../components/Mermaid.astro';
---

<Layout title="Competitive landscape" description="Where Needle sits in the market.">
  <h1>Competitive landscape</h1>

  <h2>What Needle is</h2>
  <p>
    A macOS app that coaches you through the moment you switch from one task or meeting to the next.
    It interrupts at the hard stop, clears your head, and starts you clean — with a rotating
    intervention kit so habituation doesn't kill the nudge.
  </p>

  <h2>Differentiation</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Acts at the transition</strong> — not plan-ahead or capture-after</li>
    <li><strong>Interrupts on purpose</strong> — opposite of OS "reduce interruptions"</li>
    <li><strong>Rotating kit</strong> — moat against wallpaper timers</li>
    <li><strong>macOS-native, local-first</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Calm, not aggressive</strong> — coach, not streak machine</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Position map</h2>
  <Mermaid
    chart={`quadrantChart
    title Competitive position
    x-axis Low planning --> High planning
    y-axis Low in-moment --> High in-moment
    Needle: [0.85, 0.9]
    Apple Focus: [0.2, 0.15]
    Sunsama: [0.7, 0.25]
    Llama Life: [0.5, 0.35]
    ADHD Focus Mate: [0.4, 0.75]`}
  />

  <h2>Tier 1 — Focus-state intervention</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Product</th><th>Overlap</th><th>Needle differs</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>ADHD Focus Mate</td><td>AI nudges on distraction</td><td>Fires at transitions + brain-dump ritual</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Centered</td><td>Distraction detection in session</td><td>Coaches switch between sessions</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Brain.fm</td><td>Transition ritual science</td><td>Content, not enforcing app</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Tiers 2–6 (summary)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Timers</strong> (Llama Life, Tiimo) — you start them; static habituation</li>
    <li><strong>Body doubling</strong> (Focusmate) — needs scheduled partner</li>
    <li><strong>Daily planners</strong> (Sunsama, Akiflow, Motion) — optimize the plan, silent at switch</li>
    <li><strong>OS focus</strong> — hides interruptions</li>
    <li><strong>Capture / second brain</strong> — adjacent under transition-coach thesis</li>
  </ul>

  <p><a href="/product/daily-flow/">Daily flow direction →</a></p>
</Layout>
